<br>
Second.. my rant.. or whatever.<br>
<br>
I thought long and hard about where to put this. Should it go into the private parts of my guild's board? No, I bitch too much there already. Should it go in my rockin' fun zone? No.. it's not rockin' or fun. So I came home to the soapbox. <br>
<br>
Tomorrow, as anyone knows, is September 11th. And the wound is reopened. <br>
<br>
Like my brothers and sisters in New York, I am sure the week long rememberance .. celebration of life.. whatever you want to call it.. has just about got me under my bed again.<br>
<br>
A small amount of background, for those playing along at home.<br>
<br>
I work for the Department of Defense, Missile Defense Agency. I work in the FoB 2.. which means Federal Office Building 2. Federal Office Building 1 is the Pentagon, which is right across the street. I could spit on it from my office if I didn't think I'd get shot. I go over there a lot, their food court is so much better than ours. <br>
<br>
So I was there Wed and I had some time to kill, so I just wandered about some. And panic struck me. Again. I get lost easily, and I got turned around, and I wondered what I would do if something happened again. I have little faith in the security systems. I won't get into why. My mind raced back to that day. While I was not actually there, I know the people that were. The plane that hit the pentagon was so close above the 3 story building I work in it knocked off an antenna and busted the windows.<br>
<br>
People were confused. <br>
<br>
Working next to Arlington Cemetary Flybys are common.. a couple a week. Missing man formation for some higher up. <br>
<br>
Now they have to give us warning. One woman quit my office because of it. Another drinks heavily still. One gets deathly silent when my boss makes the announcement that a flyby will be occuring that day. <br>
<br>
I have a mask at my desk. It was issued to me by the Department of Defense, and I have to return it when I quit or leave. It is what will keep me alive while everyone around me dies. I look at it and shudder, wondering sometimes if it should stay vaccum sealed. <br>
<br>
The word terrorist  denotes spreading terror of some kind. Their act was not for the damage they caused that one day. Their damage was for those who did survive, to have to relive that hell over and over again. To call frantically to try to find your father, as he was flying from Atlanta to JFK that morning. To listen to a coworker cuss and cry when a plane flies over. To see the smoke, smell it. <br>
<br>
To sit at my desk and stare at the black bag that contains the mask that just might keep me alive. <br>
<br>
They say time heals all wounds.. but I don't know if it does. It seems to me to only deaden it. But its not healed. Not yet anyway.<br>
<br>
I'm afraid people will forget. But I don't know if that is good or bad. It defeats the terrorists.. but it also, I dunno. We need to remember this. Good came of it. We came together as a country like nothing I had ever seen before. And on this anniversary most foul, I feel another swell of pride in my country, and the forces protecting it. While I know we have our problems, I cannot deny that I love my country very much.<br>
<br>
And I long for the community I felt from the world in the time afterwards. I swelled with pride when Germany patted us on the back and let us sit down and cry for a bit, Japan and the Netherlands offering to watch the world for us. France and Britian offering us information, and South Africa offering us aid. It showed the world that we are human, just like them. We bleed, and we cry. Like every other country, EVERY, I truely believe, that we are like every other country out there. A land mass filled with good people who love their country very much.<br>
<br>
So tomorrow I'm taking the day off. I'm not going in. Perhaps I'm tired of being searched walking into my job. Getting my car opened and inspected. Tired of sitting in traffic and staring at the cops ahead looking through cars. I'm gonna take a day off, do something else. <br>
<br>
But I won't forget. <br>
<br>
Because I can't.<br>
<br>
Will<br>
